```python
import pandas as pd

df = pd.DataFrame({
    "batch": ["B1","B1","B1","B2","B2","B2","B3","B3","B3"],
    "day":   [1,2,3,1,2,3,1,2,3],
    "value_A": [10, 12, 11, 20, 21, 19, 30, 29, 31],
    "value_B": [10, 11, 13, 20, 19, 18, 28, 30, 35]
})
display(df)
```

# ÌíÄÏù¥

```python
df['abs_error'] = abs(df['value_A']-df['value_B'])
df['rel_error'] = df['abs_error']/df['value_A']
display(df)
df_kpi = df.groupby('batch').agg(
    mean_abs_error = ('abs_error', 'mean'),
    mean_rel_error = ('rel_error', 'mean'),
).reset_index()
display(df_kpi)
worst_batch = df_kpi['batch'][df_kpi['mean_rel_error'].idxmax()]
unstable_batches = df_kpi['batch'][df_kpi['mean_rel_error']>0.1]
display(worst_batch, unstable_batches)
```

```python
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
df_kpi_sorted = df_kpi.sort_values(by='batch')
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7,4))
color = np.where(df_kpi_sorted['batch']==worst_batch, 'red', 'gray')
ax.bar(df_kpi_sorted['batch'], df_kpi_sorted['mean_rel_error'], color = color)
ax.set_title("Relative Error by Batch")
ax.set_xlabel("Batch")
ax.set_ylabel("Mean Relative Error")
ax.grid(False)
ax.axhline(0.1, color = 'gray', linestyle='--', linewidth=2)
plt.show()
```
